## User Flows and Navigation

### Primary User Flows

1. **Homepage Visit Flow:**
   - User lands on hero section
   - Scrolls down to view About section
   - Continues to Journey timeline
   - Reviews Skills section
   - Reaches Contact section
   - Clicks social links or scrolls to footer

2. **Navigation Flow:**
   - User clicks navigation link
   - Smooth scroll to target section
   - Active state updates in navigation
   - Section comes into view with fade-in animation

3. **Social Link Flow:**
   - User clicks social link (LinkedIn, GitHub, etc.)
   - Opens in new tab
   - Returns to portfolio

### Navigation Structure

- **Main Navigation:** Fixed header with links to Home, About, Journey, Skills, Contact
- **Footer Navigation:** Links to same sections plus copyright
- **Smooth Scroll:** All navigation uses smooth scroll behavior
- **Active States:** Current section highlighted in navigation

### Link Patterns

- **Internal Links:** Smooth scroll to sections, no underline by default, underline on hover
- **External Links:** Open in new tab, same styling as internal links
- **Social Links:** Button-style with icon, hover effect with color inversion

## Responsive Design Patterns

### Mobile (< 768px)

**Layout Changes:**
- Navigation collapses to hamburger menu
- Hero title scales down (clamp function handles this)
- Timeline padding reduced
- Skills grid becomes single column
- Social links stack vertically
- Container padding reduced (1.5rem)

**Typography:**
- Font sizes use clamp() for responsive scaling
- Line heights adjusted for mobile readability
- Reduced letter spacing on large headings

**Spacing:**
- Section padding reduced (4rem instead of 6rem)
- Reduced gaps in grids
- Tighter spacing in timeline

### Tablet (768px - 1024px)

**Layout Changes:**
- Navigation remains horizontal
- Skills grid becomes 2 columns
- Timeline maintains full width
- Container padding: 2rem

**Typography:**
- Moderate scaling between mobile and desktop
- Maintains readability

### Desktop (> 1024px)

**Layout Changes:**
- Full navigation visible
